name: Typhoon Haiyan Relief Aid Limited Edition Print #5 of 5 Cars "Soul Release"
description:
As you all know Typhoon Haiyan Unfortunately Rocked the Philippines several days ago. In an Effort to continue sending items, and many other things overseas joining various sources and other partners, here at Motolyric we are helping in our own effort. We will make a Limited Run of 10 Prints of a Chosen Car we took at SEMA 2013 and for every Order we will Donate $10 of the Sale to UNICEF!! Then the Remaining $30 will be used to Buy Food and Supplies for Relief Aids Locally!!

Each Print is a BIG 20x30 High Resolution Print backed by a Hard Foam Board for easy mounting or for Best Results Ready to Frame!! Standard FREE Shipping (USA Only), and we will include a License Plate Frame, Sticker Set, and a Smaller Limited Edition Art Poster! No watermarks on the Final Print and All Prints will be signed, numbered and #typhoonhaiyan on the bottom right corner instead. 

Only 10 will be Sold per Car Print and that's it! So get a Cool Limited Motolyric Print and Help those in Need!!

name: "Keep Calm and Don't Let Off" T-Shirt
description:
A term I've been using lately, and it was generated from something I witnessed in the past 6 months shooting Drag Cars, Drifters, Time Attackers, and even Street Racers. Whatever racing event I was shooting the hardest of the hardcore drove the hell out of their cars. The craziest experience I remember was when a friend and well known Drag Racer Santos Renovales was lining up at Fontana a few years ago with his beastly Corolla. Well he doesn't like to Let Off the Pedal, matter of fact once the lights drop on the tree he nails that pedal and doesn't let go.. Lol.. From that moment on he along with many I started witnessing where doing the same and having the best times of their lives. Racing comes with many abilities being good at it is one thing, but taking it like it yours every single time is a whole another story.... So therefore simply stated "Dont Let Off".

100% Cotton and Thick T-Shirts available in M, L, XL, XXL

$26.00 with FREE STANDARD SHIPPING anywhere in the USA. Comes with Sticker.

name: Live Free Top
description: For the females that make our lives that much better. The Live Free Female Top is simple and comfortable, yet stylish for anyone. Wash with care or don't it doesn't matter the design won't change and we've already test washed them a 100 times so we can bring you something that will last. When your done use it as a rag for your ride.

name: Motolyric Bumper Stickers
description:
Motolyric Bumper Stickers!! $8.00 Each Style or $12.00 for Both Styles.. These have derived from the very popular Slap Bumper Stickers you normally see on Drift Rides and some Track Machines, they have been very popular in Japan and have sprouted everywhere internationally from street cars to race cars. A statement for reason or none, it's a culture piece within the industry, and for the most part a way to represent a piece of passion. Intentionally they had some or no purpose but they grew to being a very popular addition to cars. Now you can get ours that do mean something and it represents clearly what we are about in a simple statement.. Established in 2010 we are MOTOLYRIC and we DON'T LET OFF!

Free Shipping Anywhere in the US

name: Bisi 911
description: The rear end of most cars are dull, but come across Legendary Tuner Bisi Ezerioha's Porsche 911 and the rear end of this beautifully executed machine becomes the only thing you want to look at. The 2012 represents the year I captured this lovely piece of art.

name: The '32
description: The OG 32 aka Deuce Coupe was one of my all time favorite cars growing up, a furious machine back in the day and still lives in the hearts of many enthusiasts thumping down local car meets and drag strips. It's a Cult Classic and a memorable piece of Automotive History.
